Business Brief -- Lukens Inc.:
   Stock Surges on Prospect
   Of End to 4-Month Strike
Details of the agreement weren't to be released until the
local's 1,338 members review it today; a ratification vote
will follow. The union is seeking improved wages and
benefits, enhanced retirement benefits and protection against
the use of nonunion labor at its main plate-steel plant.
   Lukens, Coatesville, Pa., also makes highway and
industrial safety products and provides corrosion-protection
services.